The 2026 LVMH Prize finalists have been revealed. This year's nine nominated designers highlight the growing global scope of the fashion industry, featuring young, independent brands that hail from the United States, China, Europe, and for the first time ever, Kenya. A number of new members have joined the competition's illustrious jury as well, including Michael Rider of @celine, @loewe designers Jack McCollough and Lazaro Hernandez, and @emiliopucci artistic director @camillemiceli.
The nine competing finalists are:
@colleenallen by Colleen Allen, United States
@_de_pino by Gabriel Figueiredo, France
@institution_official by Galib Gassanoff, Georgia
@juliekegels by Julie Kegels, Belgium
@l__i_i Zane Li, China
@petrafagerstrom by Petra Fagerström, Sweden
@__ponte__ by Harry Pontefract, United Kingdom
@thevxlley by Daniel del Valle Fernandez, Spain
@yoshita1967 by Anil Padia, Kenya
"The finalists demonstrated a singular creative vision while offering highly sophisticated interpretations of traditional craftsmanship," said LVMH director Delphine Arnault in a statement today. "I warmly congratulate the finalists and look forward to welcoming them to the LVMH Prize final, which will be held at the Fondation Louis Vuitton in Paris."

